  "texts": [
    "Systems designed to ensure safe interactions between humans and large language models (LLMs) * Primary and equal contributors.",
    "generally adopt one of two strategies.",
    "The first strategy includes alignment-based approaches like reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) (Ouyang et al., 2022; Bianchi et al., 2023) and Constitutional AI (Bai et al., 2022b) which embed adherence to ethical guidelines within the model parameters.",
    "Both techniques are resourceintensive and require predefined classifications of harmful content.",
    "Despite these efforts, aligned models remain susceptible to various vulnerabilities (Bhardwaj and Poria, 2023; Varshney et al., 2023), and achieving an optimal balance between safety and helpfulness remains an active research challenge."
  ],
